        <h2 id="morph-help-title" class="morph-help__title">How to use the morphology explorer</h2>
        <div class="morph-help__body">
          <section class="morph-help__sec">
            <h3>Three modes</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>🌳 Word</strong> — one word's tree. The mini-lesson below explains how the pieces nest, what each affix does, and why it matters for reading and spelling.</li>
              <li><strong>🔗 Morpheme</strong> — pick any morpheme tag (prefix, suffix, root, or lexeme); every word in the bank that contains it appears on the board with magenta links between matching pieces. The lesson becomes a Structured Word Inquiry primer: meaning, etymology, <strong>word sums</strong> showing how it builds, decoding tip, spelling rule, words in this bank, contrasting morphemes to <strong>compare with</strong>, student inquiry prompts, and a 30-second teaching move.</li>
              <li><strong>⚖ Compare</strong> — two word trees side-by-side. Magenta arcs trace the morphemes they share; the lesson is a dual “what these have in common” card.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
          <section class="morph-help__sec">
            <h3>Mouse / touch</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Drag</strong> the board to pan. The viewer auto-fits the visible trees so you don’t need to zoom manually.</li>
              <li><strong>Hover</strong> a sphere for its gloss, category, and parent word.</li>
              <li><strong>Click</strong> a morpheme sphere — if that morpheme appears in 2+ words, jumps to <strong>Morpheme</strong> mode for that piece.</li>
              <li><strong>Double-click</strong> anywhere — refit the camera.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
          <section class="morph-help__sec">
            <h3>Keyboard</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><kbd>1</kbd> Word · <kbd>2</kbd> Morpheme · <kbd>3</kbd> Compare</li>
              <li><kbd>F</kbd> or <kbd>R</kbd> — refit camera</li>
              <li><kbd>[</kbd> / <kbd>]</kbd> — smaller / larger mini-lesson text · <kbd>Alt</kbd>+<kbd>0</kbd> resets</li>
              <li><kbd>Escape</kbd> — close help</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
          <section class="morph-help__sec">
